sense.s:
Any of the stages of Hell [whereof every one except the lowest is imagined to be like a cover over another]. (TA.) [And in like manner, Any of the Seven Heavens:] one says, AlsRamewaAtu TibaAqN, meaning The Heavens are [composed of stages] one above another; (S, O, Msb; *) every heaven [except the lowest] being like a Tbq to another: (Msb:) or this is said because of their being conformable, one with another: (K:) and it is said in the Kur lxvii. 3, AalRaciI xalaqa saboEa samewaAtK TibaAqFA, meaning [Who hath created seven heavens] placed one above another; 
								TbAqA being the inf. n. of TaAbaqotu AlnRaEola [q. v.], used as an epithet; or for Tuwbiqato TibaAqFA; or caAta TibaAqK, pl. of TabaqN or of 
							TabaqapN↓. (Bd.)

[biAlTRariyqi 
								AlOawolaI is a phrase of frequent occurrence, app. post-classical; lit. By the fitter way; meaning with the stronger reason; 
								à fortiori: see an ex. in Beyd xlii. 3, and De Sacy's Anthol. Gr. Ar. p. 467.]

TaAXa AlsRahomu, (S, Msb,) inf. n. TayoXN, (A, Msb, K,) The arrow passed beyond the butt: (A, K:) or declined, or turned aside, 
								Eani Alhadafi 
								from the butt; (S, Msb;) and did not hit it. (Msb.)

Also, both epithets, but the latter has an intensive signification, An arrow that declines, or turns aside, 
								Eani Alhadafi 
								from the butt; and does not hit it. (Msb.)
